    &lt;Title&gt;Sigmoidoscopy examination&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;ppl0&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I attended the Gastroenterology Unit for a Sigmoidoscopy examination with great trepidation. I was admitted on time, everything was explained to me in a private room by an experienced and caring nurse and within half an hour I was taken to the treatment room. In the treatment room I was set at ease by the doctor that performed the procedure and the two nurses that helped with calming my nerves, encouraging me, the gas and air and maintained my dignity during the procedure. Great work by all the staff.  
The only improvement I would make is I was asked to complete a questionnaire on my medical history when I first arrived in reception, I feel that this would be better sent out with the appointment letter so that it could be better completed and brought to the appointment on the day.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
